Title: A simple remark on three dimensional gauge theories

Authors: V.E.R. Lemes, C. Linhares de Jesus, C.A.G. Sasaki, S.P. Sorella,

L.C.Q.Vilar, O.S.VenturaComments: 8 pages, LateX2e file

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B418 (1998) 324-328

Classical three dimensional Yang-Mills is seen to be related to thetopological Chern-Simons term through a nonlinear but fully local and covariantgauge field redefinition. A classical recursive cohomological argument isprovided.